Based on this, we decided to go with 3 phases. The X axis shows specific months - 0 is March 2019 and 24 is February 2021. Phase 1 (pre-covid) is march 2019 (0) - February 2020 (11). Phase 2 (crisis) is March 2020 (12) - May 2020 (14). Phase 3 (mitigation) is June 2020 (15) - February 2021 (24). We decided to make a third phase because, after June 2020, the pre-covid pattern of hours each month resumes (just at a lower level).

Unconditional Model

ran_int <- lmer(Hours ~ 1 + (1 | ID), data = abacov)

summary(ran_int)

fixed effect: Y00 is 59.38. The estimated grand mean of hours for all participants is 59.38

random effect: Uij = 620.7 is the deviation between jth individual and the grand mean. Eij = 1085.5 this is the deviation of the ith timepoint from the mean hours received by a child.

ICC calculation

620.7/(620.7 + 1085.5)
## [1] 0.3637909

The proportation of the variance in hours of therapy utillization that is due to between participant differences is .364.

Design Effect

Design effect = 1 + (average cluster size - 1) x ICC

mean(table(abacov$ID))
## [1] 24

mean cluster size = 24

1 + 23*.3638
## [1] 9.3674

design effect = 9.3674
